text: 29 is a year in the 1st century. It was a common year starting on Saturday of the Julian calendar. At the time, it was known as the Year of the Consulship of Geminus and Geminus. == Events == *Romans capture Sofia. *Agrippina the Elder is exiled to the island of Pandataria. Her sons (except Caligula) are imprisoned by Sejanus. * Possible date - Jesus baptized by John the Baptist. * Possible date - John the Baptist was beheaded by King Herod Antipas. == Births == * == Deaths == *Livia, wife of Caesar Augustus Category:29
